README for clamtk-gnome
-----------------------
Last updated 6 Aug 2016

clamtk-gnome is a simple plugin to allow a right-click,
context menu scan of files or folders.

To manually install it:
Ensure ClamTk is installed. You'll need version 4.00 or newer.
Copy the clamtk-gnome.desktop file as follows:
# cp clamtk-gnome.desktop /usr/share/applications/
You will need to have root privileges for that step.

DEPENDENCIES
------------
clamtk >= 4.00
nautilus-python

